# Environment Variables

Copy to `.env.local` and fill in values from your Supabase project dashboard.

```bash
# WorkOS AuthKit (required for production identity)
WORKOS_API_KEY=sk_test_...
WORKOS_CLIENT_ID=client_...
WORKOS_COOKIE_PASSWORD= # min 32 chars — openssl rand -base64 24
NEXT_PUBLIC_WORKOS_CLIENT_ID=client_...
NEXT_PUBLIC_WORKOS_REDIRECT_URI=http://localhost:5173/api/auth/callback

# Supabase (required)
NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_URL=https://your-project.supabase.co
NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=your-anon-key

# Supabase service role — server-only, never expose to browser
SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY=your-service-role-key

# Inngest (required for background jobs in production)
INNGEST_EVENT_KEY=
INNGEST_SIGNING_KEY=

# Modal ML compute (optional — required for GAN training jobs)
MODAL_ML_COMPUTE_URL=
MODAL_API_TOKEN=

# Edge function secrets (set in Supabase Dashboard → Edge Functions → Secrets)
# OPENROUTER_API_KEY=
# NVIDIA_API_KEY=

# Sentry (optional — error monitoring)
NEXT_PUBLIC_SENTRY_DSN=https://<key>@o<orgId>.ingest.sentry.io/<projectId>
# CI/CD only — source map uploads (never expose to browser)
SENTRY_AUTH_TOKEN=
```

## Rotation recommendations

| Variable | When to rotate |
|----------|----------------|
| `NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY` | If exposed in a public repo or client bundle leak |
| `SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY` | Immediately if ever committed or logged; quarterly otherwise |
| `INNGEST_SIGNING_KEY` | On team member departure or suspected compromise |
| `MODAL_API_TOKEN` | On team member departure or suspected compromise |
| `OPENROUTER_API_KEY` / `NVIDIA_API_KEY` | Rotate via Supabase Edge Function secrets dashboard |

## Removed (Phase 1.5)

- `NEXT_PUBLIC_SKIP_AUTH` — demo auth bypass removed
- `VITE_SUPABASE_URL` / `VITE_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY` — Vite SPA decommissioned
